def: The principles of those adhering to the house of Bourbon;obstinate conservatism.
Sidelong; on the side; laterally; also, obliquely; askew.A fellow nailed up maps . . . some sideling, and others upside down.Swift.
A liquor composed of vegetable acid, especially lemon juice,and sugar, with spirit to preserve it.
An equal, as in rank, age, prowess, etc.; a companion; acomrade; a mate.And him thus answer 'd soon his bold compeer. Milton.
See Galloway. [Scot. garron or gerron. Jamieson.]
An instrument for measuring the force or amount of endosmoticaction.
